Package neureka.ndim

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AbstractTensor.Unsafe<T>
    Tensors should be considered immutable, however sometimes it is important to mutate their state for performance reasons.
    Filler<T>
    Implementations of this ought to map the index of a tensor entry to a value which should be placed at that entry position.
    NDimensional
    This interface defines the most essential methods of the tensor API, which describe the tensor with respect to its dimensionality.
    TensorAPI<V>
    This interface is part of the Tsr API, and it defines how data can read from and written to a tensor.
    TsrConstructor.API
    An interface defining methods for configuring a Tsr in the making...
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractTensor<C,​V>
    This is the precursor class to the final Tsr class from which tensor instances can be created.
    AbstractTensor.Utility
    Static utility methods for the NDArray.
    NDimensional.Util  
    TsrConstructor
    The TsrConstructor is an internal API for receiving a wide range of different inputs and using them to populate the fields of freshly instantiated Tsr instances.
